    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hey @k06a thanks for reaching out. What are you looking to do, exactly? You can get that behavior for `truffle test` if you do `truffle test --dry-run`. If you looking for `truffle develop` to fork another network, you can modify your truffle-config.js to include a `develop` network:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  /* ... rest of truffle-config.js ... */\r\n  networks: {\r\n    /* ... rest of networks ... */\r\n    develop: {\r\n      fork: \"https://<infura-maybe?>\"\r\n      network_id: 1 // make sure this matches the forked network! (so 1 for mainnet)\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHopefully that helps! Let us know if that'll cover your use case.",
